{
  "page": "Lord Toad",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\">Lord Toad</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Alias</th><td>\nLord Toad</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">House Lannister</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Westermen\" title=\"Westermen\">Westermen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Lord Toad</b> was a <a href=\"/index.php/Fool\" title=\"Fool\">fool</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Casterly Rock\">Casterly Rock</a> during the time of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Gerold_Lannister\" title=\"Gerold Lannister\">Gerold the Golden</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf761_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf761-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> His real name is unknown.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance\">Appearance</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_Toad&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Lord Toad was a hunchback. He was old, and had a scathingly acidic wit.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf761_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf761-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_Toad&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>When the grieving Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Gerold_Lannister\" title=\"Gerold Lannister\">Gerold Lannister</a> retreated into his books and bedchamber, Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Ellyn_Reyne\" title=\"Ellyn Reyne\">Ellyn Reyne</a>, the wife of Lord Gerold's heir, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Tion_Lannister\" title=\"Tion Lannister\">Tion</a>, held sway at the court of <a href=\"/index.php/Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Casterly Rock\">Casterly Rock</a>. Ellyn hosted splendid <a href=\"/index.php/Tourney\" title=\"Tourney\">tournaments</a> and balls, and used her new position to empower her own <a href=\"/index.php/House_Reyne\" title=\"House Reyne\">house</a>. Her brothers <a href=\"/index.php/Roger_Reyne\" title=\"Roger Reyne\">Roger</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Reynard_Reyne\" title=\"Reynard Reyne\">Reynard</a> were ever at her side, and Ellyn lavished them with offices, honors, and lands. She did similar with her cousins, uncles, and other kin. Lord Toad, Gerold's fool, was heard to say, <i>\"Lady Ellyn must surely be a <a href=\"/index.php/Magic\" title=\"Magic\">sorceress</a>, for she has made it rain inside the Rock all year.\"</i><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf761_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf761-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> According to a semi-canon source, when Ellyn heard the jape, she commanded that Lord Toad be <a href=\"/index.php/Whipping\" title=\"Whipping\">whipped</a>. As Lord Gerold was too sick to interfere, and Ser Tion was too in love to refuse his wife anything, it was done.<sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After Ser Tion was killed in the <a href=\"/index.php/Fourth_Blackfyre_Rebellion\" title=\"Fourth Blackfyre Rebellion\">Fourth Blackfyre Rebellion</a>, his younger brother <a href=\"/index.php/Tytos_Lannister\" title=\"Tytos Lannister\">Tytos Lannister</a> became Lord Gerold's new heir.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf761_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf761-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> According to a semi-canon source, Lord Toad rejoiced that the <i>\"Reign of the Reynes\"</i> was over.<sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Per that same source, Lady Ellyn made an attempt to cling to her position, claiming to be pregnant by Ser Tion, but as months passed, she was seen to be a liar. Lord Toad was merciless in his mockery of Ellyn, angering Roger Reyne,<sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> who soon departed Casterly Rock for <a href=\"/index.php/Castamere\" title=\"Castamere\">Castamere</a>, accompanied by his brother and many of the other Reynes.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf761_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf761-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After Ellyn unsuccessfully attempted to seduce Tytos to convince him to set aside his wife, Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Jeyne_Marbrand\" title=\"Jeyne Marbrand\">Jeyne Marbrand</a>, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Gerold_Lannister\" title=\"Gerold Lannister\">Gerold Lannister</a> had Ellyn hastily wed to the widowed <a href=\"/index.php/Walderan_Tarbeck\" title=\"Walderan Tarbeck\">Walderan Tarbeck</a>, the fifty-five-year-old Lord of <a href=\"/index.php/Tarbeck_Hall\" title=\"Tarbeck Hall\">Tarbeck Hall</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf761_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf761-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> an extremely fat man who Lord Toad described as a \"walrus\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Lord Toad later called the bitter and ugly rivalry between Lady Ellyn Tarbeck and Lady Jeyne Lannister the <i>\"<a href=\"/index.php/War_of_the_Wombs\" title=\"War of the Wombs\">War of the Wombs</a>\"</i>, as they competed to provide their husbands with heirs.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf761_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf761-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>According to a semi-canon source, it was Lord Toad who dubbed Lord Tytos Lannister as \"the Laughing Lion\" for his jovial nature. Years after both Tytos's and Lord Toad's deaths, <a href=\"/index.php/Gerold_Lannister\" title=\"Gerold Lannister\">Gerold Lannister</a>, Tytos's youngest son, observed that Lord Toad would have been a better lord than his father.<sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_Toad&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Ellyn_Reyne\" title=\"Ellyn Reyne\">Ellyn</a> must surely be a <a href=\"/index.php/Magic\" title=\"Magic\">sorceress</a>, for she has made it <a href=\"/index.php/House_Reyne\" title=\"House Reyne\">rain</a> inside <a href=\"/index.php/Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Casterly Rock\">the Rock</a> all year.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf761_1-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf761-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;Lord Toad</cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>A wallowing <a href=\"/index.php/Walrus\" title=\"Walrus\">walrus</a> of a man. If bellies were brains, he might have been the wisest man in all <a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">the west</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_2-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;Lord Toad, about <a href=\"/index.php/Walderan_Tarbeck\" title=\"Walderan Tarbeck\">Walderan Tarbeck</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Tytos_Lannister\" title=\"Tytos Lannister\">My lord father</a> would have made a splendid innkeep, but old Toad would have been a better <a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">lord</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_2-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Gerion_Lannister\" title=\"Gerion Lannister\">Gerion Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_Toad&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf761-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf761_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf761_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf761_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf761_1-3\">1.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf761_1-4\">1.4</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf761_1-5\">1.5</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf761_1-6\">1.6</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf761_1-7\">1.7</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Seven Kingdoms&#58; The Westerlands&#32;(House Lannister Under the Dragons).</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-sample-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-sample_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-sample_2-1\">2.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-sample_2-2\">2.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-sample_2-3\">2.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-sample_2-4\">2.4</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-sample_2-5\">2.5</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-sample_2-6\">2.6</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>: The Westerlands (unabridged). <a class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.georgerrmartin.com/world-of-ice-and-fire-sample/\">georgerrmartin.com</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404000931\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.076 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.251 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 1140/10000